Using the "Cache-Control: must-understand" response directive
with a status code that the cache understands
must override the "Cache-Control: no-store" response directive.

-- cache.txt --
GET http://www.example.com/foo HTTP/1.1
Date: Sat, 01 Jan 2000 00:00:00 GMT

HTTP/1.1 200 OK
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=utf-8
Content-Length: 15
Cache-Control: max-age=604800, no-store, must-understand
ETag: "xyzzy"
Date: Sat, 01 Jan 2000 00:00:00 GMT

Hello, World!
GET http://www.example.com/foo HTTP/1.1
Date: Sat, 01 Jan 2000 00:00:05 GMT

HTTP/1.1 200 OK
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=utf-8
Content-Length: 15
Cache-Control: max-age=604800, no-store, must-understand
ETag: "xyzzy"
Date: Sat, 01 Jan 2000 00:00:00 GMT
Age: 5

Hello, World!
-- server.txt --
GET http://www.example.com/foo HTTP/1.1
Host: www.example.com
Date: Sat, 01 Jan 2000 00:00:00 GMT

HTTP/1.1 200 OK
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=utf-8
Content-Length: 15
Cache-Control: max-age=604800, no-store, must-understand
ETag: "xyzzy"
Date: Sat, 01 Jan 2000 00:00:00 GMT

Hello, World!
